 March 23 , 1916 Thursday Reviell at 5.15 Teed up at 5.30 had breakfast at 6 . Boot saddl at 6.30 , the boy then trek out 5 mile to a larg palm grove where the hors are to be kept dure the heat of the day . I went out at lunch time took their dinner out . The day was fright hot I got burnt some whilst ride . The aviat peopl have got an aerodrom fix up about 2 mile N of our camp machin have been up all day . Have had anoth attack of fever or rather the after effect am now not feel too good , went over to the Doctor but I onli got pill I do n't think lead opium is much good for counter-act fever . Turn in at 9.30 . March 24 , 1916 Friday Reviell at 5.15 Just the same procedur as of yesterday , noth els . Had a few trip out to the station , heard that there was a mail expect Down is to go to Cairo to reliev Green who has gone to the the CO is contempl a trip to Cairo if so I may stand a chanc of anoth trip . Weather still fright hot whip of fli . Metcher ( Owen brother ) came back today from hospit , he look none the wors for wear after his stay on Hell . Went up the town for a donkey ride , had supper then turn in at 9.20 .
